-- Oil Drops 0.8% in New York After Biggest Gain in Three Years
-- B y   B e n   S h a r p l e s
-- 2012-07-02T00:24:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/oil-drops-0-8-in-new-york-after-biggest-gain-in-three-years.html
Oil fell as much as 0.8 percent in
New York after rising the most in three years June 29.  Futures for August delivery slid as much as 68 cents to
$84.28 a barrel in electronic trading on the  New York Mercantile
Exchange  and were at $84.37 at 10:24 a.m. in Sydney.  To contact the reporter on this story:
